Title: The Nightingale
Author: Kristin Hannah
My Review: This book absolutely broke me, but I couldn’t put it down. It is definitely the best book I’ve read this year and I encourage everyone to read it.

Title: We Begin at the End
Author: Chris Whitaker
My Review:
I expected more from this book considering the rating, and it took me a long time to get into it and feel connected to the characters.

The last 10-20% was excellent, filled with twists and turns but to wait that long for something exciting was a bit much.

I only persevered because it was a book club read.

Title: A Thousand Splendid Suns
Author: Khaled Hosseini
My Review: This is one of my favourite books of all time. It is brilliant and heart-wrenching. Because of this book I will buy every book this guy writes...if only he wrote more often.

Author: Peter Thiel

Author: Eric Ries

Title: Wish You Were Here
Author: Jodi Picoult
My Review:
Well-written, engaging and a great storyline with an incredible twist!

I didn't realise how emotional it would be to read a book about the pandemic while still in the midst of it - if you're sensitive to the graphic details of severe covid cases, I would maybe wait a bit before reading.

Title: The Giver of Stars
Author: Jojo Moyes
My Review:
Jojo Moyes writes so beautifully and this book kept me captivated from beginning to end. I wasn't completely satisfied with how the romantic plot line panned out for the protagonist - I think I may have expected more, knowing Moyes for her 'Me Before You' series.

I did love that this book was based on a true story and that it unpacked some really interesting historical topics. As much as this wasn't my favourite, Moyes writing is so good, I will continue to read whatever she puts out.
